# {{.Name}}

A skit-based HTTP service scaffolded by `skit new --full`.

## Run locally

```bash
go mod tidy
docker compose up -d          # postgres (+ rabbitmq)
go run . migrate up
go run . serve                # GET /healthz, /readyz, /hello
```

Configuration is 12-factor: every flag has an env var (see `.env.example`).
Copy it to `.env` for local development.

## Layout

| Path | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `internal/cmd` | `serve` / `migrate` / `version` subcommands (go-flags) |
| `internal/app/config` | configuration: one struct → flags + env + `--help` |
| `internal/app/deps` | lazy dependency container + ordered initializers |
| `internal/app/server` | router build, route install, supervised runnables |
| `internal/migrations` | embedded goose SQL migrations |
| `core/<entity>` | domain business logic + Postgres store |
| `api/<entity>` | REST transport (typed handlers) |

Add a domain module with `skit add rest <name>`, then wire its store/core/handler
in `internal/app/deps` and its routes in `internal/app/server`.
